This was from user. The developer will need to decide if we do this, and if we do, how far to go with it. It would be interesting to look at infragistics and other grids, to see what they do.


Current behavior
You can currently set filters for multiple columns using:

let hardcodedFilter = {
country: ['Ireland', 'United States'],
age: {type: 'lessThan', filter: '30'},
athlete: {type: 'startsWith', filter: 'Mich'},
date:{type: 'lessThan', dateFrom: '2010-01-01'}
};

gridOptions.api.setFilterModel(hardcodedFilter);
gridOptions.api.onFilterChanged();

Desired behavior
The current code essentially ANDs all those conditions together - it would be great if you could do more complex filters - at least via the API - I can see how doing anything but AND via the current GUI would be problematic, but API or a new filter GUI in the Toolpanel could allow more advanced options - API only is sufficient for my needs at the moment:

// ActB gt 0 or ActP gt 0

let basicor = {
ActB: {type: 'greaterThan', filter: '0'},
ActP: {type: 'greaterThan', filter: '0'},
Operand: 'or'
}

// ActB eq 0 and ActP eq 0 and (NumB gt 0 or NumP gt 0)

let complex = {
ActB: {type: 'equal', filter: '0'},
ActP: {type: 'equal', filter: '0'},
Sub1: [{ NumB: {type: 'greaterThan', filter: '0' }, { NumP: {type: 'greaterThan', filter: '0' }, Operand: 'or' ]
Operand: 'and'
}

I just put the subquery in an array to easily differentiate it - there might be a better way. I'm migrating a project from infragistics silverlight grid to ag-grid and need this feature because we have quite a few complex filters saved away we'd like to keep.

It looks like this would be a small self contained change to rewrite doesFilterPass in filterManager.ts - which I might attempt assuming I can figure out how to build everything but wanted to check if there was an easier way and/or get feedback on my approach? (One minor problem I see with above is if they had a column with Operand as the colId, that would be problematic but how likely is that).


Also here:

https://www.ag-grid.com/forum/showthread.php?tid=5531
